More walls, more bars, more guards.

753
00:55:51,019 --> 00:55:53,086
我仍请您恩准  一周一信
I'd like to try, with permission. A letter a week.

754
00:55:54,006 --> 00:55:56,079
-总会有结果  -难说哦
-They can't ignore me forever.  -Sure can.

755
00:55:57,007 --> 00:55:59,073
想写就写吧
But you write your letters if it makes you happy.

756
00:56:00,004 --> 00:56:02,063
我一定寄出  行吗?
I'll even mail them for you. How's that?

757
00:56:04,031 --> 00:56:07,010
安迪开始一周一信
So Andy started writing a letter a week...

758
00:56:07,031 --> 00:56:08,090
他说话算话
just like he said.

759
00:56:13,008 --> 00:56:15,071
不过  就像诺顿说的
And like Norton said...

760
00:56:15,092 --> 00:56:17,041
毫无回音
Andy got no answers.

761
00:56:25,059 --> 00:56:30,050
次年  他替半数的警卫报税
The following April, he did tax returns for half the guards at Shawshank.

762
00:56:31,083 --> 00:56:34,010
再过一年  全都找他帮忙
Year after that, he did them all...

763
00:56:34,034 --> 00:56:36,027
包括典狱长的
including the warden's.

764
00:56:38,001 --> 00:56:41,046
再过一年的狱际棒球赛
Year after that, they rescheduled the intramural season...

765
00:56:41,068 --> 00:56:44,011
改在与税季重叠
to coincide with tax season.

766
00:56:45,068 --> 00:56:50,014
各监狱的警卫都带税单找他
The guards on the opposing teams all remembered to bring their W-2s.

767
00:56:50,035 --> 00:56:51,068
狱方发枪给你...
So Moresby Prison...

768
00:56:51,089 --> 00:56:54,015
但要你付钱
issued you a gun, but you paid for it.

769
00:56:54,039 --> 00:56:56,008
连枪套也要我付
Right. The holster too.

770
00:56:56,029 --> 00:56:58,078
这笔钱可扣除
That's tax-deductible. You can write that off.

771
00:56:58,096 --> 00:57:01,099
没错  安迪就像家庭工业
Yes, sir! Andy was a regular cottage industry.

772
00:57:02,070 --> 00:57:07,019
税季繁忙时  还可请助手
In fact, it got so busy at tax time, he was allowed a staff.

773
00:57:07,047 --> 00:57:09,096
请帮我拿一叠表格
Could you hand me a stack of 1040s?

774
00:57:10,014 --> 00:57:14,097
每年此时我调离工厂  我乐到心坎里
Got me out of the wood shop a month out of the year, and that was fine by me.

775
00:57:16,021 --> 00:57:19,037
至于信  他仍继续寄
And still, he kept sending those letters.

776
00:57:24,015 --> 00:57:27,018
瑞德  安迪  布鲁克出事了
It's Brooks.

777
00:57:28,032 --> 00:57:29,081
守着门
Watch the door.

778
00:57:30,006 --> 00:57:31,039
布鲁克
Please, Brooks.

779
00:57:31,066 --> 00:57:33,046
-你他妈的别冲动嘛  -混帐  退后
-Calm the fuck down.  -Stay back!

780
00:57:33,090 --> 00:57:36,052
-混蛋  退后!  -怎么了?
-Stay back, goddamn it!  -What's going on?

781
00:57:36,073 --> 00:57:39,029
好好的  突然亮刀子
One second he's fine, then out come the knives.

782
00:57:39,050 --> 00:57:41,030
布鲁克  有话好说
We can talk about this, right?

783
00:57:41,057 --> 00:57:45,030
放屁  没啥可说  我要割断他喉咙
There's nothing to talk about. I'll cut his fucking throat.

784
00:57:45,057 --> 00:57:47,030
等一下  赫伍哪里不对?
What's he done to you?

785
00:57:47,051 --> 00:57:49,017
错在他们
It's what they done!

786
00:57:49,068 --> 00:57:50,094
我别无选择
I got no choice.

787
00:57:51,041 --> 00:57:53,071
谁都知道你不会伤害他  对吗?
You won't hurt Heywood. We all know that.

788
00:57:53,092 --> 00:57:56,041
-对  我了解  -为何你不会伤害他?
-Right, Heywood?  -Sure.

789
00:57:56,062 --> 00:57:59,095
因为他是朋友  而你明理
He's a friend of yours, and Brooks is a reasonable man.

790
00:58:00,022 --> 00:58:01,099
-有道理  对不对?  -对
Right, guys?

791
00:58:02,026 --> 00:58:04,078
布鲁克  看着我  放下刀
So put the knife down. Look at me.

792
00:58:05,003 --> 00:58:07,026
那就把刀放下
Put the knife down.

793
00:58:09,020 --> 00:58:11,029
布鲁克  你瞧他的脖子
Look at his neck, for God's sake.

794
00:58:12,003 --> 00:58:14,037
他都流血了
Look at his neck. He's bleeding.

795
00:58:15,027 --> 00:58:16,076
只有闯祸...
It's the only way...

796
00:58:16,094 --> 00:58:19,000
才能留在牢里
they'd let me stay.

797
00:58:19,027 --> 00:58:21,064
怎么会?  别做傻事
This is crazy. You don't want to do this.

798
00:58:21,088 --> 00:58:23,094
把刀放下吧
Put it, put it down.

799
00:58:32,072 --> 00:58:34,021
放轻松一点
Take it easy.

800
00:58:34,089 --> 00:58:36,045
不会有事的
You'll be all right.

801
00:58:36,063 --> 00:58:39,012
他没事  我呢?
Him? What about me?

802
00:58:39,029 --> 00:58:41,069
老疯狗差点割断我喉咙
Crazy old fool damn near cut my throat!

803
00:58:41,090 --> 00:58:43,080
你刮胡子不也刀刀见血
You've had worse from shaving.

804
00:58:44,000 --> 00:58:46,009
你怎样惹毛他的?
What did you do to set him off?

805
00:58:46,030 --> 00:58:48,053
哪有  我只是来道别
Nothing. I come in here to say farewell.

806
00:58:49,014 --> 00:58:51,080
上面准他假释了
Ain't you heard? His parole's come through.

807
00:58:54,001 --> 00:58:56,094
我实在搞不明白
I just don't understand what happened in there.

808
00:58:57,015 --> 00:58:59,094
这老家伙简直疯了
Old man's crazy as a rat in a tin shithouse.

809
00:59:00,015 --> 00:59:02,005
赫伍  住口
That's enough out of you.

810
00:59:02,025 --> 00:59:04,098
-听说你吓的屁滚尿流  -滚你的
-Heard he had you shitting your pants. -Fuck you.

811
00:59:05,025 --> 00:59:06,045
别斗嘴了
IKnock it off.

812
00:59:07,042 --> 00:59:08,086
布鲁克没疯
Brooks ain't no bug.

813
00:59:09,029 --> 00:59:10,038
他只是...
he is just...

814
00:59:12,069 --> 00:59:14,046
体制化了
institutionalized.

815
00:59:15,083 --> 00:59:17,077
什么鸟词儿嘛
"Institutionalized," my ass.

816
00:59:17,097 --> 00:59:21,096
他坐了50年的牢  50年呀
The man's been in here 50 years, Heywood, 50 years!

817
00:59:22,017 --> 00:59:23,090
成了井底之蛙
This is all he knows.

818
00:59:24,011 --> 00:59:26,040
他念过书...
In here, he's an important man...

819
00:59:26,061 --> 00:59:27,070
在狱中有地位
an educated man.

820
00:59:28,051 --> 00:59:30,044
出狱就成了废人
Outside, he's nothing.

821
00:59:31,031 --> 00:59:34,081
双手犯关节炎的囚徒
Just a used-up con with arthritis in both hands.

822
00:59:35,002 --> 00:59:38,001
想向图书馆借书都会被拒
Probably couldn't get a library card if he tried.

823
00:59:38,029 --> 00:59:40,002
这样说你懂吗?
You know what I'm trying to say?

824
00:59:40,029 --> 00:59:43,019
我才不懂你的满嘴屁话
I do believe you're talking out of your ass.

825
00:59:44,046 --> 00:59:46,069
随你怎么说
You believe whatever you want.

826
00:59:47,030 --> 00:59:49,070
监狱是怪地方
But I tell you these walls are funny.

827
00:59:51,030 --> 00:59:52,096
起先你恨它
First you hate them.

828
00:59:54,080 --> 00:59:56,070
然后习惯它
Then you get used to them.

829
00:59:58,064 --> 01:00:00,063
更久后...
Enough time passes...

830
01:00:01,031 --> 01:00:03,030
你离不开他
you get so you depend on them.

831
01:00:04,031 --> 01:00:06,051
这就叫体制化
That's "institutionalized."

832
01:00:06,072 --> 01:00:08,001
狗屎
Shit.

833
01:00:08,022 --> 01:00:10,098
-我才不会呢  -是吗?
-I could never get like that. -Oh, yeah?

834
01:00:11,085 --> 01:00:14,034
等你待到布鲁克那把年纪 你就知道了
Wait till you've been here as long as Brooks.

835
01:00:14,059 --> 01:00:16,015
说的太对了
Goddamn right.

836
01:00:18,073 --> 01:00:20,066
他们把你关一辈子
They send you here for life...

837
01:00:21,033 --> 01:00:23,066
你的一生都被剥夺了
that's exactly what they take.

838
01:00:25,040 --> 01:00:27,039
至少是一大部分
Part that counts, anyway.

839
01:00:35,001 --> 01:00:37,095
杰克  我无法再照顾你
I can't take care of you no more, Jake.

840
01:00:39,011 --> 01:00:40,078
走吧  你自由了
You go on now.

841
01:00:42,002 --> 01:00:43,051
自由了
You're free.

842
01:00:44,079 --> 01:00:46,034
自由了
You're free.

843
01:01:05,037 --> 01:01:07,004
一切顺利  布鲁克
Good luck, Brooksie.

844
01:01:09,034 --> 01:01:11,040
保重

845
01:01:45,001 --> 01:01:46,050
亲爱的牢友...
Dear fellas:

846
01:01:46,078 --> 01:01:50,098
外头的变化快的难以置信
I can't believe how fast things move on the outside.

847
01:01:52,029 --> 01:01:54,095
老头子  嫌命长呀
Watch it, old-timer! Want to get killed?

848
01:01:56,019 --> 01:01:59,068
小时候我只看过一辆汽车
I saw an automobile once when I was a kid...

849
01:02:00,033 --> 01:02:02,076
如今...满街都是
but now they're everywhere.

850
01:02:06,044 --> 01:02:10,074
整个世界忙成一团
The world went and got itself in a big damn hurry.

851
01:02:26,056 --> 01:02:30,032
上面安排我...
The parole board got me into this halfway house...

852
01:02:30,063 --> 01:02:32,029
在中途之家
called "The Brewer"...

853
01:02:32,049 --> 01:02:33,065
并在超市...
and a job...

854
01:02:33,086 --> 01:02:36,083
当包装员
bagging groceries at the Food-Way.

855
01:02:38,037 --> 01:02:40,080
工作辛苦  我很努力
It's hard work and I try to keep up...

856
01:02:41,000 --> 01:02:43,037
但双手一直犯疼
..but my hands hurt most of the time.

857
01:02:43,067 --> 01:02:45,064
叫他务必用双层袋
Make sure your man double-bags.

858
01:02:45,084 --> 01:02:47,087
上次差点撑破袋子
Last time, the bottom near came out.

859
01:02:48,054 --> 01:02:51,048
确定要用双层袋
Make sure you double-bag like the lady says. understand?

860
01:02:51,068 --> 01:02:53,005
是  没问题
Yes, sir. Surely will.

861
01:02:53,025 --> 01:02:56,078
店长不怎么喜欢我
I don't think the store manager likes me very much.

862
01:02:59,079 --> 01:03:04,009
下工后我去公园喂鸟
Sometimes after work, I go to the park and feed the birds.

863
01:03:04,053 --> 01:03:06,002
盼望...
I keep thinking...

864
01:03:06,026 --> 01:03:09,059
杰克来打个招呼
Jake might just show up and say hello.

865
01:03:10,020 --> 01:03:12,019
但他没出现过
But he never does.

866
01:03:13,040 --> 01:03:18,027
不管他在何处  我祝他过的好  有新朋友
I hope, wherever he is, he's doing okay and making new friends.

867
01:03:21,088 --> 01:03:24,061
我夜间难以入眠
I have trouble sleeping at night.

868
01:03:24,091 --> 01:03:28,018
做着从高处坠落的恶梦
I have bad dreams like I'm falling.

869
01:03:28,045 --> 01:03:30,068
醒时恐惧莫名
I wake up scared.

870
01:03:30,089 --> 01:03:35,012
有时记不起身在何方
Sometimes it takes me a while to remember where I am.

871
01:03:36,063 --> 01:03:41,053
也许我该持枪抢劫
Maybe I should get a gun and rob the Food-Way so they'd send me home.

872
01:03:41,083 --> 01:03:46,016
毙了店长  重回肖申克  杀了他锦上添花
I could shoot the manager while I was at it. Sort of like a bonus.

873
01:03:47,084 --> 01:03:51,083
我老的无法再胡闹了
I guess I'm too old for that sort of nonsense anymore.

874
01:03:52,007 --> 01:03:53,080
我不喜欢这里
I don't like it here.

875
01:03:54,001 --> 01:03:58,000
我厌倦成天担惊受怕
I'm tired of being afraid all the time. I've decided...

876
01:03:58,085 --> 01:04:00,051
于是  我决心不再逗留
not to stay.

877
01:04:11,043 --> 01:04:13,099
当局不会在乎我...
I doubt they'll kick up any fuss...

878
01:04:14,020 --> 01:04:17,069
一个糟老头算什么
not for an old crook like me.

879
01:05:04,071 --> 01:05:07,024
老布来此一游
Brook was here

880
01:05:20,016 --> 01:05:24,043
当局不会在乎我  一个糟老头算什么
"I doubt they'll kick up any fuss, not for an old crook like me.

881
01:05:25,047 --> 01:05:29,030
替我向赫伍道歉
P.S. Tell Heywood I'm sorry I put a knife to his throat.

882
01:05:29,050 --> 01:05:31,084
别记恨在心
No hard feelings. Brooks."

883
01:05:42,032 --> 01:05:44,029
他还不如老死在肖申克好
He should have died in here.

884
01:05:49,082 --> 01:05:51,022
你在干什么?
What the fuck have you done?

885
01:05:51,043 --> 01:05:54,009
一片混乱
It's a goddamn mess, I'll tell you that.

886
01:05:59,063 --> 01:06:03,037
-这些是什么?  -你说呢  全是寄给你的
-What's all this?  -You tell me. They're addressed to you.

887
01:06:04,064 --> 01:06:05,097
你看
Take it.

888
01:06:14,052 --> 01:06:16,001
杜弗伦先生
"Dear Mr. Dufresne:

889
01:06:17,015 --> 01:06:19,012
鉴于你一再询问...
In response to your inquiries...

890
01:06:19,032 --> 01:06:23,059
本州特拨款给贵图书馆
the state has allocated the enclosed funds for your library project."

891
01:06:24,036 --> 01:06:26,019
金额两百元
This is $ 200.

892
01:06:26,039 --> 01:06:30,039
另外  主管单位...
"In addition, the library district has generously responded...

893
01:06:30,060 --> 01:06:33,016
特地捐赠旧书及杂物
with a donation of used books and sundries.

894
01:06:33,037 --> 01:06:37,050
相信可满足阁下需要  就此结案
We trust this will fill your needs. We now consider the matter closed.

895
01:06:37,071 --> 01:06:39,050
请勿再来信
Please stop sending us letters."

896
01:06:39,074 --> 01:06:42,040
典狱长回来前清干净
Clear all this out before the warden gets back.

897
01:06:42,064 --> 01:06:43,080
是的
Yes, sir.

898
01:06:48,008 --> 01:06:49,024
干的好  安迪
Good for you, Andy.

899
01:06:52,022 --> 01:06:53,035
哇!
Wow!

900
01:06:54,056 --> 01:06:56,049
只写了六年
It only took six years.

901
01:06:58,006 --> 01:07:00,079
现在起我一周两信
From now on, I'll write two letters a week instead of one.

902
01:07:01,000 --> 01:07:04,033
你真够固执的  听队长的话...
I believe you're crazy enough.  Get this stuff out...

903
01:07:04,060 --> 01:07:07,003
把东西清干净  我去撇大条
like he said.I've got to pinch a loaf.

904
01:07:07,024 --> 01:07:08,073
别让我出来...
When I come back...

905
01:07:08,090 --> 01:07:10,067
再看到这些
this is all gone, all right?

906
01:07:37,097 --> 01:07:39,063
贾各头漫划

907
01:07:59,042 --> 01:08:00,082
安迪  什么声音?
Do you hear that?

908
01:09:09,056 --> 01:09:10,072
杜弗伦
Dufresne!

909
01:09:13,026 --> 01:09:14,079
安迪  放我出去
Andy, let me out!

910
01:09:17,077 --> 01:09:19,013
安迪
Andy

911
01:09:21,067 --> 01:09:26,061
我从未搞懂她们唱什么
I have no idea to this day what those two Italian ladies were singing about.

912
01:09:26,091 --> 01:09:29,014
其实我也不想弄懂
Truth is, I don't want to know.

913
01:09:29,034 --> 01:09:31,084
此时无言胜有言
Some things are best left unsaid.

914
01:09:35,042 --> 01:09:38,015
她们唱出...
I like to think it was something so beautiful...

915
01:09:38,035 --> 01:09:40,048
难以言传的美
it can't be expressed in words...

916
01:09:40,069 --> 01:09:43,059
美的令你心碎
and makes your heart ache because of it.

917
01:09:45,026 --> 01:09:47,075
歌声直窜云端
I tell you, those voices soared...

918
01:09:48,003 --> 01:09:52,033
超越失意囚徒的梦想
higher and farther than anybody in a gray place dares to dream.

919
01:09:52,053 --> 01:09:55,090
宛如小鸟飞入牢房
It was like a beautiful bird flapped into our drab cage...

920
01:09:56,010 --> 01:09:58,087
使石墙消失无踪
and made those walls dissolve away.

921
01:09:59,031 --> 01:10:01,050
就在这一瞬间
And for the briefest of moments...

922
01:10:01,071 --> 01:10:04,070
肖申克众囚仿佛重获自由
every last man at Shawshank felt free.

923
01:10:07,028 --> 01:10:09,094
典狱长可发飚了
It pissed the warden off something awful.

924
01:10:11,025 --> 01:10:12,024
开门
Open the door.

925
01:10:15,016 --> 01:10:16,092
开门呀
Open it up!

926
01:10:18,023 --> 01:10:20,096
杜弗伦  开门
Dufresne, open this door!

927
01:10:22,030 --> 01:10:23,049
关掉
Turn that off!

928
01:10:30,057 --> 01:10:33,001
我警告你  关掉
I am warning you. Turn that off!

929
01:10:47,012 --> 01:10:49,009
杜弗伦
Dufresne

930
01:10:50,076 --> 01:10:52,028
敬酒不吃吃罚酒
You're mine now.

931
01:10:59,073 --> 01:11:02,097
安迪被罚囚两周
Andy got two weeks in the hole for that little stunt.

932
01:11:03,017 --> 01:11:04,076
站起来
On your feet.

933
01:11:05,094 --> 01:11:08,034
-看谁来了  -大指挥家
-Hey, look who's here.  -Maestro!

934
01:11:10,011 --> 01:11:13,077
你没别的可放吗?  比如汉克威廉斯的歌
You couldn't play something good, huh? Like Hank Williams?

935
01:11:14,012 --> 01:11:16,091
来不及接受点歌就被逮了
