1495
01:51:15,078 --> 01:51:18,022
别让大家等你
Come out. You're holding up the show!

1496
01:51:21,035 --> 01:51:24,075
别让大家等你  等我找上来你就没命
Don't make me come down or I'll thump your skull for you!

1497
01:51:32,033 --> 01:51:36,017
我还得等你一个  你敢耽搁我时间
Damn it, you're putting me behind!I got a schedule to keep.

1498
01:51:36,037 --> 01:51:39,067
你若没死没病  就倒霉了
You'd better be sick or dead in there.I shit you not!

1499
01:51:39,087 --> 01:51:41,020
听见没有?
You hear me?

1500
01:51:47,031 --> 01:51:49,041
我的老天爷
Oh, my Holy God.

1501
01:52:06,040 --> 01:52:08,096
这一区每人都要问
I want every man on this cellblock questioned.

1502
01:52:09,040 --> 01:52:11,096
-先从他朋友开始  -谁?
-Start with that friend of his. -Who?

1503
01:52:12,014 --> 01:52:13,054
他
him

1504
01:52:14,054 --> 01:52:16,010
打开237房
Open 237.

1505
01:52:19,061 --> 01:52:23,027
什么叫做他不见了?  这算什么鬼话?
What do you mean, "He just wasn't here"?Don't say that to me.

1506
01:52:24,015 --> 01:52:25,048
你再说就试试看
Don't tell me that again.

1507
01:52:25,068 --> 01:52:26,071
但他真的不见了
But sir, he wasn't.

1508
01:52:26,095 --> 01:52:30,041
我知道  我没眼睛吗?
I can see that, Haig!Think I'm blind?

1509
01:52:31,009 --> 01:52:32,049
你说我...
Is that what you're saying?

1510
01:52:32,069 --> 01:52:35,035
-没长眼睛吗?  -不敢  长官
-Am I blind, Haig? -No, sir!

1511
01:52:36,026 --> 01:52:38,075
你呢? 你没长眼睛吗?
What about you. You blind?

1512
01:52:39,026 --> 01:52:41,082
-你说这是什么?  -昨晚的点名单
-Tell me what this is. -Last night's count.

1513
01:52:42,003 --> 01:52:45,033
上面明明写着杜弗伦
You see Dufresne's name there?I sure do. Right there.

1514
01:52:45,054 --> 01:52:46,087
"杜弗伦"
"Dufresne."

1515
01:52:48,054 --> 01:52:50,003
熄灯时...
He was in his cell...

1516
01:52:50,024 --> 01:52:51,027
他在房里
at lights out.

1517
01:52:51,044 --> 01:52:54,038
早上也应该在才对
Reasonable he'd be here in the morning.

1518
01:52:54,071 --> 01:52:56,034
把他找到
I want him found.

1519
01:52:56,055 --> 01:53:00,001
一刻不能拖  现在找
Not tomorrow, not after breakfast. Now!

1520
01:53:00,025 --> 01:53:01,045
是的
Yes, sir.

1521
01:53:02,045 --> 01:53:06,025
搜人去  快点
Let's go. Move your butts.

1522
01:53:08,013 --> 01:53:09,012
站住
Stand.

1523
01:53:10,056 --> 01:53:11,062
你说?
Well?

1524
01:53:15,007 --> 01:53:16,006
说什么?
Well, what?

1525
01:53:16,027 --> 01:53:19,073
你们俩成天粘在一起
I see you two all the time.You're thick as thieves, you are.

1526
01:53:20,081 --> 01:53:22,030
他一定说过什么
He must have said something.

1527
01:53:23,004 --> 01:53:24,057
报告典狱长
No, sir, Warden.

1528
01:53:24,091 --> 01:53:25,090
没有
Not a word.

1529
01:53:27,075 --> 01:53:30,031
那真是奇迹了
Lord, it's a miracle!

1530
01:53:30,092 --> 01:53:33,048
人像屁一般凭空消失
Man vanished like a fart in the wind.

1531
01:53:34,015 --> 01:53:35,031
不见踪影
Nothing left...

1532
01:53:36,015 --> 01:53:38,088
只剩一堆石头
but some damn rocks on a windowsill.

1533
01:53:39,009 --> 01:53:41,082
还有墙上那骚货
And that cupcake on the wall.Let's ask her.

1534
01:53:42,003 --> 01:53:43,079
问她吧  也许她知道
Maybe she knows.

1535
01:53:44,003 --> 01:53:46,076
你说呀  短裤妞儿
What say there, fuzzy-britches?Feel like talking?

1536
01:53:48,020 --> 01:53:49,050
她不会说的
Guess not.

1537
01:53:50,007 --> 01:53:52,026
别人不说  为何她要说
Why should she be any different?

1538
01:53:53,034 --> 01:53:55,000
没错  你们有预谋
This is a conspiracy.

1539
01:53:55,064 --> 01:53:57,047
就是这样
That's what this is.

1540
01:53:58,008 --> 01:54:01,081
一个超级大阴谋
One big, damn conspiracy!

1541
01:54:02,008 --> 01:54:04,007
每个人都有份
And everyone's in on it!

1542
01:54:04,072 --> 01:54:05,088
包括她
Including her!

1543
01:54:40,092 --> 01:54:42,061
1966年...
In 1966...

1544
01:54:42,082 --> 01:54:45,022
安迪·杜弗伦逃离...
Andy Dufresne escaped...

1545
01:54:45,042 --> 01:54:46,098
肖申克监狱
from Shawshank Prison.

1546
01:54:49,023 --> 01:54:51,079
狱方只寻获泥囚衣
All they found was a muddy set of prison clothes...

1547
01:54:52,043 --> 01:54:53,096
一块肥皂
a bar of soap...

1548
01:54:54,017 --> 01:54:55,072
一把石捶
and an old rock hammer...

1549
01:54:55,093 --> 01:54:58,043
一把几乎解体的石捶
damn near worn down to the nub.

1550
01:55:02,091 --> 01:55:07,068
我曾夸口要花六百年才挖的通的隧道...
I had thought it'd take a man 600 years to tunnel through the wall with it.

1551
01:55:08,031 --> 01:55:10,094
安迪花了不到20年
Old Andy did it in less than 20.

1552
01:55:29,023 --> 01:55:31,053
他喜爱研究地质
Oh, Andy loved geology.

1553
01:55:32,030 --> 01:55:35,047
碎石令他想一探究竟
I imagine it appealed to his meticulous nature.

1554
01:55:35,087 --> 01:55:37,071
刑期如同...
An ice age here...

1555
01:55:38,014 --> 01:55:40,063
冰河时代
million years of mountain building there.

1556
01:55:41,065 --> 01:55:44,048
地质学探讨压力及时间
Geology is the study of pressure and time.

1557
01:55:45,032 --> 01:55:47,031
这就是凿通的关键
That's all it takes, really.

1558
01:55:48,005 --> 01:55:49,015
压力...
Pressure...

1559
01:55:49,079 --> 01:55:51,005
和时间
and time.

1560
01:55:52,039 --> 01:55:54,045
和一张够大的海报
That and a big goddamn poster.

1561
01:55:58,026 --> 01:55:59,042
就我说的
Like I said...

1562
01:55:59,093 --> 01:56:03,092
在牢里  没事也得找事做
in prison, a man will do anything to keep his mind occupied.

1563
01:56:06,074 --> 01:56:11,054
原来的安迪的嗜好...
Seems Andy's favorite hobby was toting his wall out into the exercise yard...

1564
01:56:12,008 --> 01:56:14,001
就是一点一滴倾倒废土
a handful at a time.

1565
01:56:15,031 --> 01:56:17,037
大概就在汤米死后...
I guess after Tommy was killed...

1566
01:56:17,058 --> 01:56:20,055
安迪决定不再久留
Andy decided he'd been here long enough.

1567
01:56:20,075 --> 01:56:23,031
动作快  我要回家
Lickety-split.I want to get home.

1568
01:56:24,006 --> 01:56:26,008
马上就好了
I'm just about finished, sir.

1569
01:56:47,055 --> 01:56:49,048
今晚要存三笔
Three deposits tonight.

1570
01:56:56,079 --> 01:56:59,009
安迪遵命行事
Andy did like he was told.

1571
01:56:59,029 --> 01:57:02,078
把鞋子擦的雪亮
Buffed those shoes to a high mirror-shine.

1572
01:57:06,047 --> 01:57:08,076
警卫都没注意
The guards simply didn't notice.

1573
01:57:09,007 --> 01:57:10,056
我也没有
Neither did I.

1574
01:57:10,074 --> 01:57:12,026
说真的
I mean, seriously...

1575
01:57:12,047 --> 01:57:15,046
谁会注意别人的鞋子
how often do you really look at a man's shoes?

1576
01:59:19,003 --> 01:59:22,019
安迪就这样爬向自由
Andy crawled to freedom through 500 yards...

1577
01:59:22,043 --> 01:59:25,077
在恶臭中匍匐五百码
of shit-smelling foulness I can't even imagine.

1578
01:59:26,077 --> 01:59:29,010
要我爬才不干
Or maybe I just don't want to.

1579
01:59:33,051 --> 01:59:35,088
五百码
Five hundred yards.

1580
01:59:36,038 --> 01:59:39,044
五座橄榄球场宽
That's the length of five football fields.

1581
01:59:40,009 --> 01:59:42,065
几乎长达半里
Just shy of half a mile.

1582
02:00:37,088 --> 02:00:42,047
次日清晨  在拉寇儿坦露她的秘密之时...
The next morning, right about the time Raquel was spilling her secret...

1583
02:00:42,078 --> 02:00:45,061
一个从未现世的人
a man nobody ever laid eyes on before...

1584
02:00:45,085 --> 02:00:48,044
走进缅因国家银行
strolled into the Maine National Bank.

1585
02:00:49,002 --> 02:00:52,018
在那之前  他不是实体
Until that moment, he didn't exist.

1586
02:00:52,076 --> 02:00:55,012
-只存在于文件上  -有何干贵?
-Except on paper. -May I help you?

1587
02:00:55,053 --> 02:00:57,046
他各种证件都有
He had all the proper ID...

1588
02:00:57,066 --> 02:01:01,036
驾照  出生证  社会保险卡
driver's license, birth certificate,Social Security card...

1589
02:01:01,080 --> 02:01:04,033
签名分毫不差
And the signature was a spot-on match.

1590
02:01:04,054 --> 02:01:07,063
失去您的生意令我真心遗憾
I must say I'm sorry to be losing your business.

1591
02:01:07,084 --> 02:01:09,057
祝您侨居愉快
I hope you'll enjoy living abroad.

1592
02:01:10,038 --> 02:01:11,047
谢谢
Thank you.

1593
02:01:12,014 --> 02:01:13,030
一定的
I'm sure I will.

1594
02:01:14,021 --> 02:01:17,055
这是银行本票  就这样吗?
Here's your cashier's check, sir.Will there be anything else?

1595
02:01:17,075 --> 02:01:18,074
麻烦你
Please.

1596
02:01:19,032 --> 02:01:21,081
帮我寄出去好吗?
Would you add this to your outgoing mail?

1597
02:01:22,032 --> 02:01:23,051
乐意之至
I'd be happy to.

1598
02:01:25,032 --> 02:01:26,065
-再会  -保重
Good day, sir.

1599
02:01:27,059 --> 02:01:32,003
那天上午史帝文斯先后去了十多家银行
Mr. Stevens visited nearly a dozen banks in the Portland area that morning.

1600
02:01:32,050 --> 02:01:34,009
总共加起来
All told, he blew town...

1601
02:01:34,030 --> 02:01:39,013
提走了诺顿的37万美金黑钱
with better than $370,000 of Warden Norton's money.

1602
02:01:39,084 --> 02:01:42,060
作为十九年冤狱的补偿
Severance pay for 19 years.

1603
02:01:49,085 --> 02:01:52,004
早上好 这里是波特兰日报
Good morning, Portland Daily Bugle.

1604
02:01:52,045 --> 02:01:54,061
肖申克监狱  贪污谋杀

1605
02:02:03,016 --> 02:02:05,065
主的审判迅速降临

1606
02:02:21,078 --> 02:02:25,018
亲爱的典狱长  你说的对  得救之道  就在其中

1607
02:02:44,090 --> 02:02:47,084
你是海利吗?  你有权保持沉默
Byron Hadley? You have the right to remain silent.

1608
02:02:48,011 --> 02:02:52,054
从现在起 你所说的一切 都将可能成为法庭上对你不利的证词
If you give up this right, anything you say can be held against you in court.

1609
02:02:52,098 --> 02:02:57,044
当时我没有在场  后来听说...
I wasn't there to see, but I hear Byron Hadley sobbed like a girl...

1610
02:02:57,065 --> 02:02:59,014
海利利被人带走的时候竟然哭得像个老娘们
when they took him away.

1611
02:03:05,002 --> 02:03:08,042
诺顿却无意乖乖就范
Norton had no intention of going that quietly.

1612
02:03:24,038 --> 02:03:25,074
诺顿
Samuel Norton.

1613
02:03:25,091 --> 02:03:28,034
诺顿  我们有逮捕令  开门
We have a warrant for your arrest. Open up.

1614
02:03:31,078 --> 02:03:34,018
把门打开
Open the door.

1615
02:03:34,072 --> 02:03:35,098
我不清楚哪一把
I'm not sure which key.

1616
02:03:45,066 --> 02:03:48,033
诺顿 拒捕是罪上加罪
Make it easy on yourself, Norton!

1617
02:03:59,058 --> 02:04:03,004
我猜他脑中最后一件事...
I like to think the last thing that went through his head...

1618
02:04:03,025 --> 02:04:04,084
除了枪子儿...
other than that bullet...

1619
02:04:05,005 --> 02:04:09,049
就是在想安迪为何能整倒他
was to wonder how the hell Andy Dufresne ever got the best of him.

1620
02:04:11,099 --> 02:04:15,045
典狱长见阎王之后不久
Not long after the warden deprived us of his company...

1621
02:04:15,073 --> 02:04:17,079
我收到一张明信片
I got a postcard in the mail.

1622
02:04:19,026 --> 02:04:22,010
没写字  但有邮戳
It was blank,but the postmark said...

1623
02:04:22,030 --> 02:04:24,043
来自德州汉考克堡
Fort Hancock, Texas.

1624
02:04:24,097 --> 02:04:26,033
汉考克堡
Fort Hancock...

1625
02:04:26,060 --> 02:04:28,033
就在边境线上
right on the border.

1626
02:04:28,074 --> 02:04:30,073
是安迪出境的地方
That's where Andy crossed.

1627
02:04:31,031 --> 02:04:35,044
一想到 他开着敞篷车 疾驶而去的神情
When I picture him heading south in his own car with the top down...

1628
02:04:35,078 --> 02:04:38,001
我就忍不住发笑
it always makes me laugh.

1629
02:04:39,085 --> 02:04:41,041
安迪·杜弗伦
Andy Dufresne...

1630
02:04:41,079 --> 02:04:43,081
终于从臭气熏天的下水道里
who crawled through a river of shit...

1631
02:04:44,002 --> 02:04:46,042
清清白白的走了出来
and came out clean on the other side.

1632
02:04:47,026 --> 02:04:48,062
安迪·杜弗伦
Andy Dufresne...

1633
02:04:49,043 --> 02:04:51,002
向太平洋驶去
headed for the Pacific.

1634
02:04:54,000 --> 02:04:56,016
海利掐住他说...
Hadley's got him by the throat, right?

1635
02:04:56,037 --> 02:05:00,017
"他活的不耐烦了"
He says, "I believe this boy's about to have himself an accident."

1636
02:05:00,037 --> 02:05:03,024
老友们常聊起他
Those of us who knew him best talk about him often.

1637
02:05:03,091 --> 02:05:05,060
他那些惊人之举
I swear, the stuff he pulled...

1638
02:05:05,081 --> 02:05:08,078
"请我朋友喝啤酒吧"
"My friends could use a couple of beers."

1639
02:05:09,011 --> 02:05:10,077
真的做到了
And he got it!

1640
02:05:12,002 --> 02:05:14,042
他走了  有时...
Sometimes it makes me sad, though...

1641
02:05:14,069 --> 02:05:16,012
令我感伤
Andy being gone.

1642
02:05:16,082 --> 02:05:20,095
有些鸟儿是不应该被关在笼子里的
I have to remind myself that some birds aren't meant to be caged.

1643
02:05:21,043 --> 02:05:23,049
因为它们的羽毛太丰润了
Their feathers are just too bright.

1644
02:05:25,020 --> 02:05:26,093
当他们飞走...
And when they fly away...

1645
02:05:27,037 --> 02:05:31,077
你会由衷地庆贺他获得自由
the part of you that knows it was a sin to lock them up does rejoice.

1646
02:05:32,084 --> 02:05:34,010
无奈的是...
But still...

1647
02:05:34,057 --> 02:05:38,091
你得继续在这乏味之地苟活
the place you live in is that much more drab and empty that they're gone.

1648
02:05:43,011 --> 02:05:45,048
我真怀念这位友伴
I guess I just miss my friend.

1649
02:06:09,094 --> 02:06:11,010
请坐
Please sit down.

1650
02:06:16,095 --> 02:06:18,051
阿里斯瑞丁
Ellis Boyd Redding...

1651
02:06:19,005 --> 02:06:22,032
根据你的材料 你的终身监禁已经服满40年
your files say you've served 40 years of a life sentence.

1652
02:06:23,012 --> 02:06:25,025
你改过自新了吗?
You feel you've been rehabilitated?

1653
02:06:27,013 --> 02:06:28,068
改过自新?
Rehabilitated?

1654
02:06:30,073 --> 02:06:32,063
噢 让我想想
Well, now, let me see.

1655
02:06:33,063 --> 02:06:35,096
我不大明白这个词的含义
I don't have any idea what that means.

1656
02:06:38,007 --> 02:06:40,033
就是说准备好重返社会
It means you're ready to rejoin society...

1657
02:06:40,091 --> 02:06:43,024
我当然明白你的意思 年轻人
I know what you think it means, sonny.

1658
02:06:45,041 --> 02:06:47,040
对我而言 这只是个术语
To me it's just a made-up word.

1659
02:06:48,075 --> 02:06:51,008
就像政治家那些术语
A politician's word so that...

1660
02:06:51,052 --> 02:06:55,004
使你们穿西装打领带的...
young fellas like yourself can wear a suit and a tie...

1661
02:06:55,052 --> 02:06:57,011
有活干
and have a job.

1662
02:06:59,009 --> 02:07:01,018
你到底想了解什么?
What do you really want to know?

1663
02:07:01,096 --> 02:07:03,093
我后悔犯罪吗?
Am I sorry for what I did?

1664
02:07:04,036 --> 02:07:05,052
你后悔吗?
Well, are you?

1665
02:07:07,043 --> 02:07:10,027
我没有一天不后悔
There's not a day goes by I don't feel regret.

1666
02:07:11,064 --> 02:07:15,009
但并非受惩罚才后悔
Not because I'm in here or because you think I should.

1667
02:07:18,058 --> 02:07:21,014
我回首前尘往事
I look back on the way I was then...

1668
02:07:23,028 --> 02:07:24,044
那个
a young...

1669
02:07:25,055 --> 02:07:29,004
犯下重罪的小笨蛋
stupid kid who committed that terrible crime.

1670
02:07:32,006 --> 02:07:33,075
我想跟他沟通
I want to talk to him.

1671
02:07:35,069 --> 02:07:38,018
我试图讲道理
I want to try and talk some sense to him.

1672
02:07:38,090 --> 02:07:40,083
让他明了
Tell him the way things are.

1673
02:07:42,093 --> 02:07:44,037
但我办不到
But I can't.

1674
02:07:46,057 --> 02:07:48,056
那个少年早就不见了
That kid's long gone...

1675
02:07:49,077 --> 02:07:52,054
只剩下我垂老之躯
and this old man is all that's left.

1676
02:07:53,095 --> 02:07:55,044
我得接受事实
I got to live with that.

1677
02:07:56,078 --> 02:07:58,048
改过自新?
Rehabilitated?

1678
02:07:58,085 --> 02:08:00,068
狗屁不通的词
It's just a bullshit word.

1679
02:08:01,062 --> 02:08:06,039
你盖章吧  别浪费我的时间
So you go on and stamp your forms,sonny, and stop wasting my time.

1680
02:08:07,063 --> 02:08:09,089
告诉你一句实话
Because to tell you the truth...

1681
02:08:10,023 --> 02:08:12,022
我他妈的不在乎
I don't give a shit.

1682
02:08:25,044 --> 02:08:27,000
核准
Approved

1683
02:09:21,070 --> 02:09:24,007
老布到此一游
Brook was here

1684
02:09:38,075 --> 02:09:40,015
谢谢你
Here you go, miss.

1685
02:09:43,009 --> 02:09:44,011
可以上厕所吗?
Restroom break?

1686
02:09:49,093 --> 02:09:54,046
别要尿尿就来报告  要去就去  懂吗?
You don't need to ask me every time you need to go take a piss. Just go.

1687
02:09:55,050 --> 02:09:57,009
是的
yes

1688
02:10:07,051 --> 02:10:10,057
我报告了40年
Forty years I've been asking permission to piss.

1689
02:10:11,042 --> 02:10:14,041
没报告  一滴也挤不出
I can't squeeze a drop without say-so.

1690
02:10:17,092 --> 02:10:20,008
我得面对残酷的事实
There's a harsh truth to face.

1691
02:10:21,076 --> 02:10:24,066
我根本混不下去
No way I'm going to make it on the outside.

1692
02:10:32,054 --> 02:10:36,023
我一心想违犯假释
All I do anymore is think of ways to break my parole...

1693
02:10:37,004 --> 02:10:39,053
也许能重返肖申克
so maybe they'd send me back.

1694
02:10:44,072 --> 02:10:47,015
活在恐惧中真是糟糕
Terrible thing, to live in fear.

1695
02:10:48,005 --> 02:10:49,071
布鲁克体会过
Brooks Hatlen knew it.

1696
02:10:49,092 --> 02:10:51,086
他看透了
Knew it all too well.

1697
02:10:53,046 --> 02:10:56,086
我只想回到有意义的地方
All I want is to be back where things make sense.

1698
02:10:57,030 --> 02:11:00,003
不必整天担惊受怕
Where I won't have to be afraid all the time.

1699
02:11:02,003 --> 02:11:04,040
只有一件事阻止了我
Only one thing stops me.

1700
02:11:05,084 --> 02:11:08,024
我向安迪做的承诺
A promise I made to Andy.

1701
02:11:28,076 --> 02:11:29,089
到了
There it is.

1702
02:11:40,050 --> 02:11:42,017
非常感谢您
Much obliged, sir.

1703
02:11:51,022 --> 02:11:53,071
巴克斯顿
Buxton

1704
02:15:21,049 --> 02:15:22,075
亲爱的瑞德
Dear Red:

1705
02:15:22,099 --> 02:15:25,048
见到这封信的时候 你已经出狱了
If you're reading this,you've gotten out...

1706
02:15:25,066 --> 02:15:29,072
既然走了这么远的路 干脆再走远一点吧
and if you've come this far,maybe you'd come a bit further.

1707
02:15:30,000 --> 02:15:32,049
你还记得那个地方的名字,是吗?
You remember the name of the town, don't you?

1708
02:15:34,077 --> 02:15:36,026
芝华塔尼欧
Zihuatanejo.

1709
02:15:37,091 --> 02:15:41,050
你能帮我实现计划
I could use a good man to help me get my project on wheels.

1710
02:15:42,001 --> 02:15:45,054
我备妥棋盘等着你
I'll keep an eye out for you,and the chessboard ready.

1711
02:15:46,035 --> 02:15:47,075
记住,瑞德.
Remember, Red...

1712
02:15:48,009 --> 02:15:50,018
心怀希望是一件好事
hope is a good thing...

1713
02:15:50,039 --> 02:15:52,038
也许是最好的事
maybe the best of things.

1714
02:15:52,059 --> 02:15:54,075
心怀希望 就永远有希望
And no good thing ever dies.

1715
02:15:55,029 --> 02:15:58,016
希望这封信 能让我再次见到你
I will be hoping that this letter finds you...

1716
02:15:58,036 --> 02:16:00,009
一个健壮的你
and finds you well.

1717
02:16:00,060 --> 02:16:01,083
你的朋友
Your friend...

1718
02:16:02,003 --> 02:16:03,019
安迪
Andy.

1719
02:16:37,003 --> 02:16:38,076
要么忙于生存
"Get busy living...

1720
02:16:38,097 --> 02:16:40,087
要么赶着去死
or get busy dying."

1721
02:16:43,057 --> 02:16:45,074
这话真他妈的精辟
That's goddamn right.

1722
02:16:48,031 --> 02:16:50,080
瑞德也来过

1723
02:16:50,098 --> 02:16:53,011
这是生平第二次
For the second time in my life...

1724
02:16:53,035 --> 02:16:55,091
我又犯了罪
I'm guilty of committing a crime.

1725
02:16:56,099 --> 02:16:58,092
违反假释出城
Parole violation.

1726
02:16:59,059 --> 02:17:03,025
我怀疑警方会设路障逮我
Of course I doubt they'll toss up any roadblocks for that.

1727
02:17:03,093 --> 02:17:05,095
我这种老贼可以免了
Not for an old crook like me.

1728
02:17:06,016 --> 02:17:08,019
德州汉考克堡
Fort Hancock, Texas, please.

1729
02:17:11,087 --> 02:17:16,060
我激动的坐不住不停地想
I find I'm so excited I can barely sit still or hold a thought in my head.

1730
02:17:17,004 --> 02:17:20,037
自由人才会这么兴奋吧
I think it's the excitement only a free man can feel.

1731
02:17:20,058 --> 02:17:23,007
踏上未知旅程的...
A free man at the start of a long journey...

1732
02:17:23,028 --> 02:17:25,087
自由人
whose conclusion is uncertain.

1733
02:17:28,089 --> 02:17:31,055
我希望成功越过边界
I hope I can make it across the border.

1734
02:17:33,006 --> 02:17:36,008
我希望能跟老友握握手
I hope to see my friend and shake his hand.

1735
02:17:37,096 --> 02:17:42,002
我希望太平洋如梦中一般蓝
I hope the Pacific is as blue as it has been in my dreams.

1736
02:17:43,087 --> 02:17:45,006
我希望...
I hope.

1737
02:18:19,020 --> 02:18:23,090
谨此纪念亚伦格林

